        caption: String.raw`5G's scalable numerology on one time axis. A subframe is always $1$ ms, but it holds $2^{\mu}$ slots: one $1$ ms slot at $\mu=0$ ($15$ kHz), two $0.5$ ms slots at $\mu=1$ ($30$ kHz), four $0.25$ ms slots at $\mu=2$ ($60$ kHz), eight $0.125$ ms slots at $\mu=3$ ($120$ kHz, mmWave). Every slot carries $14$ OFDM symbols, so doubling $\Delta f=15\cdot2^{\mu}$ kHz halves the slot and drives down latency at higher bands. The inset shows the frequency atom: a resource block is $12$ subcarriers, and a single resource element (one subcarrier on one symbol, highlighted) carries one modulation symbol — $12\times14=168$ RE per RB per slot.`
